SIMPLE: annals
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Annals
<hw>An"nals</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>annalis</ets> (sc. <ets>liber</ets>), and more frequently in the
pl. <ets>annales</ets> (sc. <ets>libri</ets>), chronicles, fr.
<ets>annus</ets> year. Cf. <er>Annual</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
relation of events in chronological order, each event being recorded
under the year in which it happened.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Annals</xex> the
revolution.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Macaulay.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>annals</xex> of
our religion.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Rogers.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Historical records; chronicles; history.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The short and simple <qex>annals</qex> of the poor.</q>
<rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It was one of the most critical periods in our
<qex>annals</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <singf>sing.</singf> <def>The record of a single event or
item.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧In deathless <xex>annal</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Young.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A periodic publication, containing records of
discoveries, transactions of societies, etc.; <as>as
⟦ldquo⟧<ex>Annals</ex> of Science.⟦rdquo⟧</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- History. See <er>History</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Annapurna</ent>⟦br⟧
